 <text>
  <front>
   <head>To Dr. Mead, on his Cape Wine.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Wine, by  Suns refin'd,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Is a just Emblem of your Mind:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Like You, the gen'rous Juice displays</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Its Influence a thousand Ways;</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Like You, it raises sinking Hearts,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Inspiring, and rewarding Arts;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Dispels the Spleen, and conquers Pain,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Calls back departing Life again.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
